taxonomy.title: Location
taxonomy.description: This facet describes where an object was created and/or found. The organization is based upon geographic and political divisions of the world.
taxonomy.notes:
For the purpose of alphabetization, leading qualifiers, adjectives, articles, etc. are ignored. For example: "Republic of Macedonia" is treated as "Macedonia"; "Peoples' Republic of China" is treated as "China"; "The Bahamas" is treated as "Bahamas"; "State of the Vatican City" is treated as "Vatican City".

taxonomy.title: Culture
taxonomy.description: This facet describes the culture(s) associated with an object (who created or used it, or is depicted). The organization combines general geographic range with cultural groupings.
taxonomy.notes:
While cultures tend to be associated with location, the range of a culture does not neatly match political boundaries. ******************** Notes for a future revision:
It might be useful to make this into more of a "who" facet. Such a "who" facet would have these major sub-facets: • Person (personal name of specific person) • Culture by geography (what this facet currently is limited to) • Culture by language group (Athabascan, Uto-Aztecan, etc.) • Profession (e.g., shoemaker, weaver) • Role (e.g., wife) • Rank (e.g., royalty, serf, slave, caste) • Gender (e.g., male, female, hermaphrodite) • Age (e.g., adult, elderly, adolescent, child)

taxonomy.title: Material
taxonomy.description: This facet describes the materials that make up an object (another aspect of what it is). The organization loosely follows the popular animal/vegetable/mineral pattern.
taxonomy.notes:
This facet particularly reflects the non-specialist audience, and follows a folk organization. The topics are mostly the same as would be present for a specialist in anthropology, but the organization and chosen labels are different.
Terms to add: Crystal Lead/leaded Crystal Foil - where would I file this?

taxonomy.title: Technique, Design or Decoration
taxonomy.description: This facet describes how an object was made, and combines visual design and decorative elements with the techniques used in creating an object. The organization is broad, reflecting a wide range of creative activities.
taxonomy.notes:
This facet and its coverage in the collections will continue to improve with time as we enrich the model.
Terms to add: • Palmetted • Guilloche (n) "architectural ornamentation resembling braided or interlaced ribbons" • Lanceolate • Peened tenon • Mortise and tenon

taxonomy.title: Color
taxonomy.description: This is a somewhat experimental facet that describes colors described for an object. This is based not on an analysis of the image, but on the description and notes for an object.
taxonomy.notes: We continue to experiment with techniques to improve the reliability of this, but it seems to be fun even with the current limitations.
